observations.recommendation:
The GSO/MT and Accounting Unit will conduct reconciliation of their respective records in order to establish the existence, status/conditions and whereabouts of the assets;
Advise the inventory team to use property tags during the count to facilitate identification and location of the PPE;
The GSO/MT and Accountant shall have to maintain Property Cards and Equipment Ledger Cards, respectively, to ensure the accuracy and reliability of the property and accounting records;
Provide adequate information on the inventory reports such as the model, serial number, cost, conditions and property number to facilitate identification during the count;
Require clearance from retired/resigned officials and employees to clear them of their property accountability and cancel the corresponding Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) for the returned items.
